# =============================================================================
# Gemini (optional — enables “Live AI” in the copilot)
# =============================================================================
#
# LOCAL DEVELOPMENT
# -----------------
# 1. Copy this file to `.env.local` (same folder as package.json).
# 2. Set GEMINI_API_KEY below to your key from Google AI Studio or Google Cloud.
# 3. Restart `npm run dev`.
# Never commit `.env.local` or paste real keys into this file.
#
# VERCEL (production / preview)
# -----------------------------
# 1. Vercel Dashboard → your project → Settings → Environment Variables.
# 2. Add `GEMINI_API_KEY` with your new API key.
#    - Enable for Production (and Preview if you want preview deploys to use AI).
# 3. Optional: add `GEMINI_MODEL` (defaults to gemini-3-flash-preview if unset).
# 4. Redeploy (or push a commit) so serverless functions pick up the new values.
#    Changing env vars alone does not update already-built functions until redeploy.
#
# Verify: open the site, open Copilot — you should see the “Live AI” badge when the key is active.

GEMINI_API_KEY=

# Optional (default: gemini-3-flash-preview). Override for other models, e.g. gemini-2.5-flash
# GEMINI_MODEL=gemini-3-flash-preview
